vectorData.altText: 20. What movement is occurring in the shoulder?
That's right!  The arm is rotating around its long axis, such that the forearm is carried laterally. This is lateral rotation.
That is incorrect. Click here      to learn the answer, and then come back to try again.

Perform these movements as illustrated, and be sure you understand them. 
Notice that medial and lateral rotation of the hip occurs around the long axis of the femur, and that medial and lateral rotation of the shoulder occurs around the long axis of the humerus.
